    "body": "Sadly, copying (syncing or whatever-ing) my application's source to a directory with Electron every time I change something is pretty lame.\n\nI tried passing my source directory as an argument to Electron by using `desiredCapabilities.chromeOptions.args`:\n\n``` javascript\nimport assert from 'assert';\nimport webdriver from 'selenium-webdriver';\nimport electronPrebuilt from 'electron-prebuilt';\nimport path from 'path';\nimport webdriverio from 'webdriverio';\n\nconst options = {\n  'host': 'localhost',\n  'port': 9515,\n  'desiredCapabilities': {\n    'browserName': 'chrome',\n    'chromeOptions': {\n      'binary': electronPrebuilt,\n      'args': [path.resolve('./src')]\n    }\n  }\n};\n\nconst client = webdriverio.remote(options);\n```\n\nWhen you do this, what happens is not:\n`electron.exe path/to/stuff`\nbut sadly is:\n`electron.exe --path/to/stuff`\nsince whatever responsible for passing the arguments appends them with \"--\".\n\nIf Electron supported something like \"--app=path/to/app\", then we could make this work.\n"
  },
